(Pixabay/stevebp) JOHANNESBURG - South Africa’s economy shrank by 1.3% in the last three months of 2022. This after growing by 1.8% in the third quarter. READ: SA's economic troubles | Greylisting will affect township economies Overall the economy grew by 2% last in 2022. Power cuts hit the major sectors, with seven industries including Mining, Agriculture, and Manufacturing declining. Economists had expected a contraction following increased power cuts, a higher cost of living, and a failing logistics network.